Yen Declines as Speculation Ebbs That Bernanke Will Signal More Stimulus

-- B y   G r e g   S t o r e y
-- 
2011-08-25T13:13:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/yen-declines-as-speculation-ebbs-that-bernanke-will-signal-more-stimulus.html
The yen fell against most of its
major counterparts as speculation ebbed that Federal Reserve
Chairman  Ben S. Bernanke  will announce further monetary stimulus
tomorrow.  The Japanese currency traded at 77.16 per dollar in  New
York .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
